  "text": "Mice were anesthetized and euthanized on day 3 or 7 after injury. Brains were removed and frozen at Ϫ20°C. Coronal sections of 20-m thickness were taken at 320-m intervals over the rostralcaudal extent of the lesion. Sections were stained with hematoxylin and eosin, and lesion volume was measured by digitally sampling stained sections with an image analyzer. Lesion volumes (mm [CITATION_1] ) were computed as running sums of lesion area multiplied by the known interval (eg, 320 m) between sections over the extent of the lesion expressed as an orthogonal projection.",
